{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/mocking-your-api","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"df83fcd8-6327-5c66-a0c5-4d61dcbac203","html":"<p>There are multiple ways to mock an http endpoint in your code. Simply, just return the sample response that you expect! This works perfectly for SOAP or HTTP or whatever endpoint you want to mock. Though they are tedious way, makes your code dirty, requires a cleanup. It is better to disassociate your mocking with actual code, especially when you are mocking HTTP endpoint. For quick mocking and development, I bring to you - 2 tools of the trade.</p>\n<h2 id=\"json-server\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#json-server\" aria-label=\"json server permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><a href=\"https://github.com/typicode/json-server\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">json-server</a></h2>\n<p>As mentioned in repository description “Get a full fake REST API with zero coding in less than 30 seconds”. It is one of the most used mocking library and for quick prototyping in Front End world. You can also mocking Backend-to-backend API calls based on JSON. Its mocked API follows REST guidelines, and what made me happy was 201 HTTP status being returned when you make a POST request. You can end up creating entire CRUD mocking on these tools.</p>\n<p>You can checkout egghead video tutorial here - <a href=\"https://egghead.io/lessons/nodejs-creating-demo-apis-with-json-server\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Creating Demo APIs with json-server</a></p>\n<p>You can literally do all functionalities that you would implement in server API as well. Routing, middleware, CRUD, full text search, sorting, etc.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/844c63ae560dc736b6a380d14802e7c9/0f96c/json-server.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 52.916666666666664%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/844c63ae560dc736b6a380d14802e7c9/8ac56/json-server.webp 240w,\n/static/844c63ae560dc736b6a380d14802e7c9/d3be9/json-server.webp 480w,\n/static/844c63ae560dc736b6a380d14802e7c9/e46b2/json-server.webp 960w,\n/static/844c63ae560dc736b6a380d14802e7c9/f992d/json-server.webp 1440w,\n/static/844c63ae560dc736b6a380d14802e7c9/882b9/json-server.webp 1920w,\n/static/844c63ae560dc736b6a380d14802e7c9/cee32/json-server.webp 2248w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/844c63ae560dc736b6a380d14802e7c9/8ff5a/json-server.png 240w,\n/static/844c63ae560dc736b6a380d14802e7c9/e85cb/json-server.png 480w,\n/static/844c63ae560dc736b6a380d14802e7c9/d9199/json-server.png 960w,\n/static/844c63ae560dc736b6a380d14802e7c9/07a9c/json-server.png 1440w,\n/static/844c63ae560dc736b6a380d14802e7c9/29114/json-server.png 1920w,\n/static/844c63ae560dc736b6a380d14802e7c9/0f96c/json-server.png 2248w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/844c63ae560dc736b6a380d14802e7c9/d9199/json-server.png\"\n          alt=\"Screenshot\"\n          title=\"Screenshot\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Official Site: <a href=\"https://github.com/typicode/json-server\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">json-server</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"mockit\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#mockit\" aria-label=\"mockit permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><a href=\"https://mockit.netlify.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">mockit</a></h2>\n<p>Another tool that I have recently come across and use it is MockIt. MockIt was designed and developed to help developers get off the ground faster, and give developers a quick way to create APIS for their applications. It gives you a user interface to configure and create REAL mocked end points for your applications.</p>\n<p>It has clean UI to build your mock routes and response. It also has delay (latency) to capture UI behavior for actual APIs that take some time. Live Reload, Chaos Engineering(via Chaos Monkey), Authentication, CORS, are some features that it offers out of the box.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/c17ce1103f763ef88677841b9b72330e/8b936/mockit.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.33333333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/c17ce1103f763ef88677841b9b72330e/8ac56/mockit.webp 240w,\n/static/c17ce1103f763ef88677841b9b72330e/d3be9/mockit.webp 480w,\n/static/c17ce1103f763ef88677841b9b72330e/e46b2/mockit.webp 960w,\n/static/c17ce1103f763ef88677841b9b72330e/338ac/mockit.webp 1368w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/c17ce1103f763ef88677841b9b72330e/8ff5a/mockit.png 240w,\n/static/c17ce1103f763ef88677841b9b72330e/e85cb/mockit.png 480w,\n/static/c17ce1103f763ef88677841b9b72330e/d9199/mockit.png 960w,\n/static/c17ce1103f763ef88677841b9b72330e/8b936/mockit.png 1368w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/c17ce1103f763ef88677841b9b72330e/d9199/mockit.png\"\n          alt=\"Screenshot\"\n          title=\"Screenshot\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Official Site: <a href=\"https://mockit.netlify.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">mockit</a></p>\n<hr>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/mocking-your-api","tagSlugs":["/tag/tools/","/tag/code/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2019-04-22T18:05:00.738Z","description":"Tools designed to help developers quickly create mock end points for their applications for faster development.","tags":["Tools","Code"],"title":"Mocking your HTTP endpoints - APIs","socialImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/mocking-your-api"}}}